The page information tab only displays page-level edit restrictions and makes no mention of space-level edit restrictions. This misleads users who meet page-level edit restrictions but not space-level edit restrictions, because they can't see why they are being blocked from editing.

For example, a space may restrict edit rights to group Alpha. One page in this space adds that users must be in group Beta as well. When a user that is just in group Beta checks to see why they can't edit the page, they are told that they sole edit criteria is to be in group Beta.

Please list space permissions for editing on the page information permissions.

