The following is a snippet of a local Tomcat's server.xml file that defines Confluence's context path:
{code:xml}
<Context path="/" docBase="../confluence" debug="0" reloadable="false">
{code}

With the above configuration, links in the "View" page mode (such as the "Edit" tab) would then be redirected to the following URL pattern:
{noformat}
http://pages/editpage.action?pageId=<the pageID>
{noformat} 

Note, where the URL has missing <Domain URL> (Please see screenshot, {{view_mode.jpg}}). The correct URL should be:
{noformat}
http://<domain URL>/pages/editpage.action?pageId=<the pageID>
{noformat}

A workaround would be to remove the / sign if Confluence is to configure to access without any context path. For example:
{code:xml}
<Context path="" docBase="../confluence" debug="0" reloadable="false">
{code}

