In version v.2.6.2, the style for links to non-existing pages was changed to drop the little green plus sign, and make the links underlined red text.

I've had several users comment that the red underline style just looks like a classic "visited" link, and doesn't make it clear that it's prompting them to create a new page. It doesn't look like there's anything special about the link.

I suggest adding back the little icon, and adding Alt Text that says something like "Create this Page."
